**Workflow:**
User -> Planner;
Planner -> FileAnalyzer;
Planner -> WebSearcher;
FileAnalyzer -> WebSearcher;
WebSearcher -> Summarizer;
Summarizer -> End.

**Description:**
1. The Planner analyzes the user's query and creates a plan for file analysis (extracting ORCID IDs) and web searching (finding pre-2020 works per ORCID). 2. The FileAnalyzer reads the JSONLD file to extract ORCID IDs. 3. The WebSearcher uses Google Search to locate each ORCID page and count pre-2020 works. 4. The Summarizer calculates the average of these counts and returns the final numeric result. **Important:** No additional user input is required.
